	Using your computer can lead to RSI or back pain if you're not vigilant. Make sure you stretch out your hands and arms regularly. Ask if your office can host a weekly yoga class for a complete body stretch out.&lt;/p&gt;" href="http://www.blogcdn.com/lifestyle.aol.co.uk/media/2011/07/stretch-hands-getty.jpg" data-photo-src="http://www.blogcdn.com/lifestyle.aol.co.uk/media/2011/07/stretch-hands-getty.jpg" data-credit="Getty">Stretch it out</a><div class="aol-photo-caption">&lt;p&gt;
	Using your computer can lead to RSI or back pain if you're not vigilant. Make sure you stretch out your hands and arms regularly. Ask if your office can host a weekly yoga class for a complete body stretch out.&lt;/p&gt;</div><img alt="Stretch it out" class="aol-gallery-photo" src="http://www.blogcdn.com/lifestyle.aol.co.uk/media/2011/07/stretch-hands-getty.jpg" /></li><li><a title="&lt;p&gt;
	When you want to talk to someone in your office, consider if you could go and talk to them in person. This gets you out of your chair and is more friendly than sending an email. It's even more effective if they don't work on the same floor as you do and you have to take the stairs.&lt;/p&gt;" href="http://www.blogcdn.com/lifestyle.aol.co.uk/media/2011/07/woman-sitting-on-desk-getty.jpg" data-photo-src="http://www.blogcdn.com/lifestyle.aol.co.uk/media/2011/07/woman-sitting-on-desk-getty.jpg" data-credit="Getty">Don't send emails all the time</a><div class="aol-photo-caption">&lt;p&gt;
	When you want to talk to someone in your office, consider if you could go and talk to them in person. This gets you out of your chair and is more friendly than sending an email. It's even more effective if they don't work on the same floor as you do and you have to take the stairs.&lt;/p&gt;</div><img alt="Don't send emails all the time" class="aol-gallery-photo" src="http://www.blogcdn.com/lifestyle.aol.co.uk/media/2011/07/woman-sitting-on-desk-getty.jpg" /></li><li><a title="&lt;p&gt;
	Avoid your office lift and take the stairs. If your meeting room or canteen is on the top floor, you'll tone your legs and burn calories running up and down the stairs instead of standing still in a cramped lift.&lt;/p&gt;" href="http://www.blogcdn.com/lifestyle.aol.co.uk/media/2011/07/woman-stairs-getty.jpg" data-photo-src="http://www.blogcdn.com/lifestyle.aol.co.uk/media/2011/07/woman-stairs-getty.jpg" data-credit="Getty">Take the stairs</a><div class="aol-photo-caption">&lt;p&gt;
