	Strap on a pedometer and set a target for the number of steps you need to take while in the office. Offer to make the coffee, organise the stationary cupboard and be the office busybody - it all helps keep you fitter than sitting like a stone at your desk.&lt;/p&gt;" href="http://www.blogcdn.com/lifestyle.aol.co.uk/media/2011/07/woman-talking-colleague-getty.jpg" data-photo-src="http://www.blogcdn.com/lifestyle.aol.co.uk/media/2011/07/woman-talking-colleague-getty.jpg" data-credit="Getty">Move around</a><div class="aol-photo-caption">&lt;p&gt;
